  "prompt": "Is there an inpatient Drug and Alcohol Rehab Center in Shasta County California?",
  "response": "Yes, Shasta County, California, offers several inpatient drug and alcohol rehabilitation centers to support individuals seeking treatment. Here are some options you might consider:\n\n### 1. **Shasta Treatment Center**\n- **Location:** Redding, CA\n- **Services:** Provides comprehensive inpatient programs for substance abuse, including detoxification, individual and group therapy, relapse prevention, and aftercare planning.\n- **Contact:** [Website](https://www.shastatreatmentcenter.com/) | Phone: (530) XXX-XXXX\n\n### 2. **Gateway Counseling Services**\n- **Location:** Redding, CA\n- **Services:** Offers residential treatment programs for addiction, including personalized therapy plans, holistic treatments, and family counseling.\n- **Contact:** [Website](https://www.gatewaycounselingservices.com/) | Phone: (530) XXX-XXXX\n\n### 3. **365 Recovery Centers**\n- **Location:** Redding, CA\n- **Services:** Provides inpatient rehab with a focus on evidence-based therapies, medical support, and comprehensive aftercare services.\n- **Contact:** [Website](https://www.365recoverycenters.com/) | Phone: (530) XXX-XXXX\n\n### 4. **Valley Health Centers**\n- **Location:** Shasta Lake, CA\n- **Services:** Offers residential treatment programs for individuals struggling with substance abuse, including mental health services and vocational training.\n- **Contact:** [Website](https://www.valleyhealthcenters.com/) | Phone: (530) XXX-XXXX\n\n### Additional Resources\n\n- **SAMHSA Treatment Locator:** The Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) offers a [treatment locator](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/) tool that can help you find accredited facilities in Shasta County and surrounding areas.\n  \n- **Local Support Groups:** Organizations like Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) and Narcotics Anonymous (NA) have meetings and resources in Shasta County that can provide support alongside professional treatment.\n\n### Tips for Choosing a Rehab Center\n\n1. **Assess Your Needs:** Consider factors like the severity of the addiction, any co-occurring mental health disorders, insurance coverage, and personal preferences regarding treatment approaches.\n   \n2. **Verify Credentials:** Ensure the facility is accredited and staffed by qualified professionals.\n\n3. **Visit the Facility:** If possible, tour the center to get a sense of the environment and amenities.\n\n4. **Ask About Aftercare:** Effective treatment plans often include aftercare services to support long-term recovery.\n\n### Get Professional Help\n\nIf you or a loved one is struggling with substance abuse, reaching out to a healthcare professional or contacting one of the listed facilities can be an essential first step toward recovery.\n\n---\n*Please note that contact information provided above is illustrative. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, please visit the respective websites or contact the facilities directly.*",
